This paper deals with a logical framework for representing state transitions in transition systems that operate under temporal, stochastic or probabilistic constraints. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories of computer science, including Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
